Connecticut Governor Dannel Malloy expresses his support for the American Jobs Act proposed by President Obama. He believes that the act will directly benefit Connecticut residents and businesses. Malloy highlights the benefits of investing in infrastructure, such as creating jobs, and funding education to prevent teacher layoffs and larger class sizes. He also emphasizes the importance of extending unemployment insurance to prevent poverty for approximately 78,000 workers in Connecticut who will exhaust their benefits by the end of the year.